summary: Can we all just appreciate the cast of Endgame? This movie was absolutely heart-breaking and the emotion portrayed by everyone...
body: Can we all just appreciate the cast of Endgame? This movie was absolutely heart-breaking and the emotion portrayed by everyone was absolutely stunning. It left me in tears. This is the end of an era, imagine how they felt after seven years of doing Avengers movies. This is the last time we’ll see them all together. This was the end, and it was an amazing few years. Now, it moves onto a different generation of heroes. We just really have to appreciate the heroes who altered our life one way or another.

summary:
•
When I hear movie fans complain about the MCU because the “stakes are meaningless” or because “they’re all the same” or...
caption: • When I hear movie fans complain about the MCU because the “stakes are meaningless” or because “they’re all the same” or because “it’s all just dudes punching each other” it really genuinely upsets me. And not because I think everyone should love Bucky Barnes as much as I do. It doesn’t upset me as an MCU fan, it upsets me as a movie fan. • Because I feel as though they’ve completely missed the point of what this series has managed to achieve. The MCU is the first of its kind in Hollywood history. When we, as fans, went to see Infinity War and then Endgame, we spent our time with countless characters that we all KNEW. And we knew them because of 11 years worth of work that made these two films that much more special. Seeing all these people on screen didn’t make me think “oh wow this movie is so bloated”. It made me insanely emotional and proud that movie making managed to take such a risk in creating a shared universe like this. • Has it produced negative results too? Of course! Nothing is perfect. But from that first moment that Nick Fury told Tony Stark he wanted to talk to him about the Avengers Initiative, this genre of movie was changed forever. Because of the hard work of thousands of people and our love for these characters, we managed to bring this genre into the spotlight and a driving force in Hollywood, both creatively and at the box office. • For me, the MCU has made film history and even though it will go on after Endgame, this movie was a perfect reminder of what the last 11 years have been about. • This is an end of an era for us MCU fans. We made it to the Endgame together. Let’s see what they’ve got in store for us next ❤️ • After all … we could do this all day. • #MCU #movies #film #avengers #avengersendgame #endgame #theavengersdemandyoursilence #dontspoiltheendgame https://www.instagram.com/p/BwtwMEIAKk_/?utm_source=ig_tumblr_share&igshid=apok0vw7cki0
